windows.question:
Which of the following best describes the anomaly detection results within the time series window spanning steps 326 to 347?
A) Downward Convex anomaly: Values form a downward convex curve that decreases more sharply than the surrounding trend.
B) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
C) Irregularly Pattern anomaly: The segment shows irregular oscillations without a stable trend.

options.A: Downward Convex anomaly: Values form a downward convex curve that decreases more sharply than the surrounding trend.
options.B: The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
options.C: Irregularly Pattern anomaly: The segment shows irregular oscillations without a stable trend.

windows.answer: C) Irregularly Pattern anomaly: The segment shows irregular oscillations without a stable trend.

windows.question:

A) Downward Spike anomaly: Values plunge dramatically in a sudden downward spike.
B) Upward Spike anomaly: There is a sharp upward jump in the measurements.
C) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.

options.A: Downward Spike anomaly: Values plunge dramatically in a sudden downward spike.
options.B: Upward Spike anomaly: There is a sharp upward jump in the measurements.
options.C: The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.

windows.answer: C) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
